messages.content: Everyone is spit back out onto the beach in 1 piece.
‚ÄúWhat the fuck?‚Äù
‚Äú‚Ä¶‚Äù I‚Äôm not entirely sure how to feel about my door, but I suppose it went as good as could be expected.
Azura coughs on the ground before struggling to her feet. She stares at Roshan, and then points at them accusingly. "You-! Why, did you, you!" Too incensed to speak.
I slowly dust myself off. "Urgh... Stupid asshole..."
‚ÄúWhat? I don‚Äôt even know how I died. I guess she just like, psychically crushed all my organs at once‚Ä¶ what???‚Äù
"‚Ä¶No, what‚Ä¶? That wasn‚Äôt‚Ä¶ I wouldn‚Äôt‚Ä¶" I‚Äôm breathing really heavily all of a sudden. Oh, no‚Ä¶
‚ÄúWhy did she bring us here for a chance to ‚Äòatone‚Äô when she killed us? Is she stupid?‚Äù
Yikes. Everyone else is having visceral reactions, and here I am just sorta chilling. ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt remember her killing me‚Ä¶‚Äù
I look over at my sister, relaxed. "I think it was more of a metaphorical death, Yaz. As in, the death of our persona."
‚ÄúI mean, it‚Äôs not all of us, yeah. ‚Ä¶Cyrus was, uh, someone else.‚Äù
"Yes, yes, you killed me, we all understand that by now."
‚ÄúBut like. She definitely intended to kill *you*. And that was the last door in time. So I‚Äôm just not dead??? What?‚Äù

Daryush sits down on the ground solemnly.

Douglas thinks about something silently.

Ebrahim looks at Johammad apologetically.

L smiles.
"Didn't you feel your memories leaving?"
"Everything was washed away for me, right then."

"No!" She cries out, shaking her head. "No, I died! You stupid fuck!" Directed at Roshan. "Haaaaugh, was it because of *Daryuuuush?* Were you just soooo jealous you had to gather a mob to lynch me to death???"
‚ÄúNo? I felt like I was being stabbed everywhere and also maybe what giving birth is like or something.‚Äù
"I assumed it was that way for you, too."
"Hm."
"No, no, no, no‚Ä¶ that wasn‚Äôt me‚Ä¶ that couldn‚Äôt have been-nnnn‚Ä¶ uuaaaah‚Ä¶"
‚ÄúMaybe she also messed with my mind that way, I can‚Äôt say confidently I would‚Äôve noticed‚Ä¶‚Äù
"Does anyone else feel like they still don‚Äôt remember certain things?" Douglas.
‚ÄúYeah, kinda. I don‚Äôt know what‚Ä¶ like, did I kill Douglas? That felt like a lie, kind of?‚Äù

I look warily to Azura, then over at Jo. I realize suddenly that we're in an awkward situation... wah. I'm acting so nonchalant... sorry, guys. I walk over to Joey and start petting him. My fingers prickle, but I make myself ignore it.
‚ÄúAbsolutely, Father.‚Äù I agree with Douglas. ‚ÄúThere‚Äôs some things that just feel‚Ä¶ without a sense of conclusion.‚Äù
Could I. Roll wisdom to attempt to parse that in my own mind?
Azura marches over to Roshan. "Hey! Fucking answer me!"
I startle. "I, um. I'm sorry, what was the question, again?"
((Sure))
‚ÄúPlease stop‚Ä¶ we can‚Äôt fight, look, Cyrus is chill even though I fucked him over‚Ä¶‚Äù
"Wwwggggh. Pl- please d-‚Ä¶" No, I can‚Äôt reject them now. It wouldn‚Äôt make sense. Just‚Ä¶ just‚Ä¶ I don‚Äôt know‚Ä¶
I scratch him behind his ears a few times.

"You killed me!" She cries out. "It was b-because of you, you just haaaaaad to let everyone know I was a whooooooore, ahaha...!" She grips her head, furious. "Why do I even care?!? I shouldn't have expected anything better from the rest of you filthy.. fucking..."
All of your memories do connect but it feels like something‚Äôs missing after your death somehow.
What she sayin fuck me for? I take a couple steps away from the conversation unfolding and just let it play out as background noise while I think.
"...yes. There is a connection point, but- something's off... something is missing after Yazmine killed me. It's not complete."
I look over to everyone. "Everyone! Please, wind down! We're not done yet! Something's missing!"
‚ÄúSorry‚Ä¶?‚Äù She looks briefly at Azura before just kind of glancing all around.

I look down uncomfortably, considering her non-question question. "I didn't think you were a whore, I'm pretty sure... that was mainly something I called your mother. The promiscuity angle is a bit confusing to me, honestly. I would do things differently if I had another chance."
‚ÄúOkay, wait, if Roshan and I didn‚Äôt die, and theres more for Cyrus after I supposedly killed him, and the death door is sometimes a metaphor‚Ä¶ are any of us even dead???? What‚Äôs going on.‚Äù

"I'm sorry, Azura. The whole thing probably wasn't worth it. I don't really know anymore. But you're fine, aren't you? You're here... Daryush is here with you. Our mistakes weren't impossible to fix."
She bursts out laughing. "I knooooooow I'm dead, for sure..!"
‚ÄúI was pretty sure too‚Ä¶‚Äù
Roshan's words, amazingly, fail to comfort her. She buries her head in her hands and bursts into tears.
"...I- I'm not dead. I think. I guess I might be."

L laughs madly and smugly. 

"What exactly is there to find funny now?" Ebrahim.

"Sorry, sorry... I did promise you all an explanation, didn't I?" L.
I awkwardly approach and stand near Azura but don‚Äôt actually do anything.
I pat Jo. "You're fine, buddy."
I turn to face L. This fucking guy‚Ä¶
I'm really not. I don't know why this isn't helping. It's terrifying.
I look to L. "Go ahead, then. Explain it."
I wander away from Jo absentmindedly, in the general direction of L.
Nooooo, you can't just... do that... come back...
‚ÄúMan. I wonder if Jafari‚Äôs okay. He was cool, even if he did fraud. It‚Äôs good to have friends who know politics so you can have opinions on things.‚Äù
"Oh, so he did do it. Thanks."
‚ÄúI don‚Äôt know if he did, I‚Äôm just going off your word.‚Äù
"Wait, huh? You- goddammit." I facepalm.

*It doesn't matter. It doesn't even fucking matter! He's right. I literally got Daryush in the end. I won. I succeeded. He's mine!!! What happened back then's irrelevant to me, now. Everything I did wrong in life I have the tools to handle now, as another, better Azura. Are these the contemptible emotions of whatever new creature inhabited this body, before I got my memories back? Her impulses, her shame, her pettiness, her weakness? Ridiculous! It's not even about her. Who cares! I ate her for breakfast and threw her away.*

Azura, still crying silently, turns her attention to Daryush. What's he doing?
The fact that I made Azura cry flicks back into my head. I feel really bad. "Ah, s-sorry, Azzy... I didn't mean to upset you... is there anything I can do to help?"
Azzy...?
...Whateverrrr...
"Azzy??"
*I‚Äôm so confused. Is there a triangle of some sort?*
"Huh? I just... like giving people nicknames, Cyrus... I've done it with a lot of people. Do you want one?"

"Sorry... There's just one last step. See... We need to summon the goddess, remember? And she doesn't come unless someone actually completes a door. That was the slight downside to keeping you all with a free door for today. We're past midnight, if you all couldn't tell." L walks up to the birth door. "So just give me a sec, y'know? It's my turn to get real."

"You have reached the door of birth. The seeds of what made you you, forever, in the center of the world. You are not tainted by any other door yet today.  Your requirement to open this door, Inmate #058, is to enter with Inmate #061 at the same time." The door speaks and yet opens anyway.

"Sorry, but... I decided 61's here." L winks at the door, an action not perceptible to any player. He vanishes through it, shutting the door behind him.

"...What the fuck?" Daryush says this about the door thing. "WHAT THE FUCK!?" He says this about the Azzy thing slightly louder.
"What the fuck????"
‚Äú‚Ä¶yeah, that‚Äôs‚Ä¶ sure, man, whatever.‚Äù
"No?"
‚ÄúWe didn‚Äôt complete a door?‚Äù I blink a few times. ‚ÄúSorry, what did he just say? Which one was 61.‚Äù
"...the one who died beforehand."
"Yeah, don't you remember, Yaz... Yazmine? We all found it together." I smile at her.
‚ÄúI thought that was 62. Hm.‚Äù
"Oh, maybe."
Ismalisa appears. She's silent.
I don't get jumpscared this time. Character development

Azura makes a pained noise, like she's been punched. "Ahahah, it's nothing, you can't do anything for me... just leave Daryush alone, okay? Don't speak to him, don't look at him, try not to think of him if you can help it...!"
‚ÄúI guess maybe two died‚Ä¶ cause there was a cave in‚Ä¶ like, the rest of us started with one other guy, I think? Maybe? No, wait, there‚Äôs 7 of us, right‚Ä¶?‚Äù I look down.
...I realize I'm on my hands and knees when I see her.
I look back up. ‚ÄúOh shit it‚Äôs Ismalisa from Ismalisa.‚Äù
"Ismalisa. What is this?"
Did Joey trip? I hope he didn't hurt himself...
Azura shakes in terror while looking up at her ~~mother~~ ~~father~~ ~~nothing~~ God.
‚ÄúHey, if I fail, do you kill me, or am I just in this place forever?‚Äù
‚ÄúAlso, why did you do like, any of that stuff. I got the major parts, it‚Äôs because you refuse to get pregnant, but still, what was up with the end there?‚Äù
"What? She didn't refuse to get pregnant."
‚ÄúDaryush being male was a problem. It literally only can be if she‚Äôs unwilling to reproduce with a male.‚Äù

"So you have all completed your lives? Are you all ready to at-" Ismalisa finally speaks up but is interrupted by a circle of podiums carved out of sandstone, one for everyone here, raising out of the ground.

"Sorry, we're not doing that. Atonement's so complex and subjective. This is a puzzle. So let's put our heads together, y'know?" L appears at one of the podiums with the same suddenness Ismalisa's apparitions have.

Azura opens her mouth, seemingly considering something, before closing it.

"...I just... she had me, all along. Neither of us were complete, but I still... wasn't good enough, for her to take me.." Azura says. What?
‚ÄúHow did he do that?‚Äù Yazmine has not understood anything for like 30 minutes or years.
"...What?" I try to stand. Feeling a little wobbly still, haha.
I call out to him. "Are you okay, Johammad?"

"Everyone get on a podium. Actually, wait... Still getting used to having my shit back." L.

You are all suddenly at your podiums.
Azura is on her podium.
"Y- yeah, I'm okay- don't- woah!"
I grab onto the podium.
Cyrus is at his podium. "Guh-"
For balance.
I keep my balance perfectly fine.
‚ÄúHoly-!‚Äù This is just like a‚Ä¶ what was it‚Ä¶ a tlass crial? No‚Ä¶

‚ÄúYeah, I guess I didn‚Äôt think about that part again with how I know it has to work now. Like‚Ä¶ I mean, whenever this started, the first holy maiden can‚Äôt have been the child of her and a maiden, so‚Ä¶‚Äù I look around in a panic, hand on my weapon. ‚ÄúIs L god? What‚Äôs happening.‚Äù
"Weh." Weh.

‚ÄúHey, wait a fucking second. If the maiden thing is a result of Ismalisa endlessly‚Ä¶ eurgh, gross, but‚Ä¶ genetically, it means the maidens are like, impossibly close to her. So why is she white?‚Äù
Daryush isn‚Äôt white, right?
Oh, my god, Yazmine, you can't just ask someone why they're white.
Wait, is Ismalisa white?
Isn‚Äôt Ismalisa white?
What IS white, really?
Is Ismalisa a woman?
What gender does this god identify as anyways?
Ismalisa is not white. No one here except Douglas and Celine are white.
Yazmine checks if she‚Äôs white.
Damn.
Woo! Go white people go!
She does look white, though. I get what she means.
"I don't think her skin is literally that color, Yazmine. That would be crazy. It's probably something metaphorical, like her being a ghost or a spirit of some kind."
‚ÄúHm.‚Äù I consider this.

"I suppose I should introduce myself officially. What do you all think a demon is?" L.

"Evil incarnate." Ismalisa glares at him.

"True, but not what I mean." L.
"...the opposite of a god, yes? Or at least, an antonym to a god and their purpose."
"Bingo! Now what's the role of a god?" L.
"To have a lot of power?"
"That's... fairly harder to discuss, but a being which exists to uphold some sort of value?"
"I... don't really know. That almost feels like it's been deliberately muddied."
‚ÄúTo be worshipped, I suppose.‚Äù

"Gods are rules. In the grand scheme of things, they represent order. So the opposite, contradictions... Mean chaos. Foundational issues that are impossible to resolve. When a god makes a mistake... We are born. Demons. Immortal beings with great powers that embody a foundational impossibility in reality. So, hehe... Allow me to introduce myself. My name is Laplace Newcomb, the Demon of Knowledge."
‚Äú‚Ä¶Ok?‚Äù I don‚Äôt get it.
I blink.
‚ÄúHow is knowledge the opposite of justice?‚Äù
....yeah, that makes sense.
Azura opens her mouth and closes it, confused.
"...I was really hoping L stood for Lisaisma." I murmur.
‚ÄúOh, that would‚Äôve been cool.‚Äù I nod at Celine.
"That would have been funny."
If he's the demon of knowledge, then how does he not know how off-putting he looks?

"I'm not the opposite of Ismalisa in particular, hah. I'm an error in the way reality functions. To keep thing simple, I know everything that ever has happened and everything that ever can happen based on everything I do. Usually this would mean manipulation, I'd be a real nice guy... But losing my memories at the start meant all I could do was slowly work my way back up in my truest personality. It's real refreshing, you know?" Laplace.

"So that's why you kept smugly saying you knew things? Because... You were predicting what would happen?" Daryush, glaring.

"Exactly! I know exactly what specific combination of actions will lead to whatever I want in the easiest or most fun way possible." Laplace.
Cyrus nods silently.
‚ÄúOh yeah? What number am I thinking of.‚Äù
It‚Äôs 4.

"4." Laplace scoffs. "Though it's honestly absurd you think that's the best my powers can do." 

"That doesn't explain your control of sinspace." Daryush.
I look slightly embarrassed.
‚ÄúShit. Okay, then who were 61 and 62??? Who shared a memory with the Demon of Knowledge? Also was Douglas lying when calling you a coworker or what.‚Äù

"I work for the AMO. It's a quid pro quo thing. And 61 and 62 don't exist. They existed to round out the number with a set of 3 since I'd been added to you all." Laplace.

"Pardon me, but a set of 3 would not make sense. 64 is not a multiple of 3." Douglas.
‚ÄúI saw a body, though??? Right? Did Islamist just make up a guy?‚Äù Autocorrect sucks but sure Yazmine canonically misspoke in universe.
"...I don't get it."

I pause and think.
‚Äú‚Ä¶Am I not supposed to be here?‚Äù
"Aren't 61 and 62 a set of two?"
‚ÄúDoes anyone have pen and paper, dang, this is like‚Ä¶‚Äù

"People come in groups of 3. Haven't you noticed? No particular meaning to it, just the structure. But since I got added to what should've been 6 people, those 2 fakes had to be added." Laplace.

Ismalisa remains silent.
"Huh?" I get a sort of dreamy look in my eyes. "Oh, yeah... I guess so, haha."

"61 and 64 are both still not multitudes of 3." Douglas.

"You're forgetting to count inmate 0." Ebrahim.

"My apologies. 62 and 65 are both still not multitudes of 3." Douglas.
"Yeah, what gives? Is there an inmate -1 we're not aware of?"
‚ÄúWhat if Ismalisas an inmate. Or something.‚Äù

"Points for Yazmine on that one. Ismalisa here's the last inmate. She's just plus 1 to whatever the highest number is. Math adds up, see? Not that this actually matters to the important questions." Laplace.
‚ÄúNice. That doesn‚Äôt make any sense at all, actually.‚Äù
‚ÄúWas the first group Ismalisa and two guys?‚Äù
"She's inmate X plus 1, with X being the maximum number of inmates here."
*Who is X????* Yazmine wonders this and then decides not to say it because it feels like she just missed something.

"It was... I think a group of 11." Ebrahim.

The wolf is at his podium, barely conscious. He is processing information but incapable of saying anything.
"I see... so I'm X." I nod.
Sorry I'm late, I was doing X.
I listen on as Laplace continues the explanation.
~~No, I think that was me.~~

"X is 10, usually..." Douglas makes a joke that may actually make no sense culturally. But it's fine he's worldly he can know this.

"The real question you all need to ponder... Is what Sinspace is." Laplace.
‚ÄúNo, then I‚Äôd be Ismalisa.‚Äù She gets it now. Maybe?
I make a mental note to invest more in the teaching programs if I ever become leader once more.
"I sort assumed we were... y'know, since the doors aren't a real physical place, this was sort of similar."
"If the goddess of Justice is an inmate as well... and, if I seem to be right, we are not dead... is this another realm?"
"Sinspace is, like, magic, right?"
"I thought you were 63, Yazmine?"
"Have you been 65 this whole time? Ah, embarrassing..."
Azura shakes her head. "But I did die.."

‚ÄúOkay, if we‚Äôre not dead, though, then, what if this is just‚Ä¶ some island, somewhere. In our world.‚Äù
She turns to Roshan and blinks.
‚Äú‚Ä¶Oh. Right. You were 4. Oops.‚Äù
((It‚Äôs so awesome how every asinine stupid mistake i make is characterization))
"I was 59!" Very helpful, Celine.
"So did I.... but there must be some catch, after all."
‚ÄúI mean. Not like I checked for a heartbeat, I mighta not done enough.‚Äù I shrug. ‚ÄúWasn‚Äôt like I cut off your head or anything.‚Äù
"Correct to the 'some island' answer. This is my home island. Though you can't see it through all the hallucination trickery." Laplace.
‚ÄúI can see it.‚Äù
"A building that was on fire collapsed with me in it. I'm... definitely dead.."
"Yeah, I agree with Yaz. You're not making any sense."
‚ÄúOkay, so you‚Äôre the one in charge of this place and Ismalisa was a trick. Or something? But also you‚Äôre trapped here. But she was trapped here first.‚Äù
"...then is Sinspace a creation of both of you?"
‚ÄúA collaboration between fated enemies‚Ä¶ it‚Äôs almost heartwarming.‚Äù Yazmine says this without a hint of irony.
"Like a baby?"
"Woah..."
"Why would you imagine a baby first!?"
‚ÄúWhat? Azura, god, everything you say you‚Ä¶ wait, how would you even come to believe that, you don‚Äôt have parents????‚Äù Her character analysis skills fall short.
‚ÄúI think I‚Äôm jumping to conclusions. What were we talking about‚Ä¶‚Äù
"The nature of Sinspace! Stop thinking about babies!"
‚ÄúI could easily defeat and escape the imprisonment of a baby.‚Äù
"Who was pregnant with Sinspace?"

Azura crosses her arms, embarrassed. "W-why wouldn't I think that?!? A living creatio of a man and a woman, umm, that's the natural conclusion to jump to, right?" She blinks at Yazmine. "I know how children are born!!! Obviously, I know that!"
‚ÄúProbably Laplace.‚Äù
"Is an island really 'living'...?"
"Are either of those even possible?"

‚ÄúI just. I didn‚Äôt say them being a man and a woman, just that they were fated enemies. So, it felt like you were sayin‚Äô every union that produced a child is between people who hate each other???‚Äù
"EVERYONE BE SILENT!" Ismalisa shouts and attempts to do something to Yazmine. It does nothing.
She twiddles with her fingers. "No! That's not what I mean, aughh... it would be a ridiculous thing for me to say, I mean, I love Daryush..."
‚ÄúAlso, Ismalisa is like, a man, somehow. I wouldn‚Äôt be surprised if Laplace also didn‚Äôt simply follow our idea of what makes a guy‚Ä¶ uhhh‚Ä¶‚Äù
I am listening to Ismalisa and being quiet like a good noodle.
I regain some focus. "Azura, you... you had a baby with Dar? Is that true?"
"Please... Be silent all of you! Listen to this demon no longer! Shut up! Please be silent! Please! Just... Just be silent this instant!" Ismalisa.
"What are we supposed to do, if you won't give any answers!?"
"I don't particularly feel like I'm listening to anyone...?"
‚ÄúNo?! What?‚Äù She turns to Roshan. ‚ÄúWhat is happening‚Ä¶‚Äù
"Ah, no, not yet..."
‚ÄúYet?!‚Äù
"Um, sorry. Should I be- um-"
...It's kind of cathartic to see Ismalisa like this, actually.
"Oh... okay. Sorry for the confusion, haha." My eyes drift away from her again.
‚ÄúOkay, look, what do the two of you even *want*???? Are we here to be lectured at by warring divines for the rest of our lives or afterlives???‚Äù
"Er. Yes? I suppose I was hoping, one day, to..." She trails off, staring at the ground.
"Warring divines?" Laplace smirks with fake confusion.
"Azura, you shouldn't... You shouldn't talk about this." Daryush.
"Ah, okay. Sorry." Azura says and shuts up and doesn't talk.
I consider saying something, but don't.

‚ÄúI won‚Äôt try to argue about your relationship, but the kid would be, like, really sick. Some soltaria noble guys messed about with that kinda thing and it ended their bloodline, I think?‚Äù She turns to Daryush. ‚ÄúThat would be convenient, right? It‚Äôs for the best that she doesn‚Äôt ever have any chance to go against you. God, I swear‚Ä¶ that last memory cemented I‚Äôm a bad guy, so‚Ä¶ ahhah‚Ä¶‚Äù Yazmine trembles.
"I think you were trying your best, Yazmine. I know I was cruel about it at the time, but I don't blame you for anything you did. I hope you know that. It all worked out in the end, anyways."
"Even if you were a bad guy before, you don't have to be now, right?"
I'm not fully aware of the context of what I'm responding to, but I try my best.
‚ÄúI don‚Äôt even know what now is. Everyone‚Äôs dead, I think? Including me, maybe?‚Äù
Azura nods. "I've already told you that I think you're a good person, Yazmine... even if I'm not the person qualified to forgive you."
"I thought the whole point of this whole spectacle was that we weren't dead."
‚ÄúThe point of this whole spectacle is that L stood for Laplace.‚Äù
"Maybe you were dead before, but you aren't now. It's like the thing about being a bad person."
"Oh, I see."

"Is this all you guys talk about? Fucking your siblings? Just kidding, I know the answer to that." Laplace.

"Everyone stop talking about romance and sex, okay!? Let's focus on whatever this puzzle he wants is." Daryush.
"Life changes. So does death, I guess. It's alright."
Didn't pick up on that one before, haha. Wow!
‚ÄúRoshan and I didn‚Äôt have sex.‚Äù Yazmine quickly clarifies.
"Focus!" I tell Yazmine.
((god yeah i was thinking the other day that joh is the one guy who has no idea about any of this shit))
"I never had relations with my sibling! Don't say that!"
"Huh????" Azura's eyes rapidly dart between Roshan and Yazmine.

‚ÄúRoshan is my sibling. Or was. Not when we were born. We‚Äôre orphans.‚Äù Yazmine assumes this is the question and answers Azura politely.
‚ÄúI mean, not by blood. And I might‚Äôve gotten sibling disowned.‚Äù
"Don't worry, it's still on the table." Laplace gives Yazmine a mocking thumbs up. It's impossible to know if he's being genuine. Because of paradoxes.
‚ÄúWhat?‚Äù
"Nobody thinks that you had sex with The Wolf, Johammad. It's okay."
"SHUT UP ABOUT SIBLINGS AND SEX AND FOCUS ON THE SUBJECT AT HAND!"
Cyrus screams this, actually sounding angry.
"N- no! He's especially not my brother, and I especially never had-" !!!
"He's not... my bro... And my bro totally..." The wolf doesn't finish that sentence because he's too weak.
Azura yelps. "Okay! S-sorry..."
((Scrunkly‚Ä¶ ü•∫ ))
Yazmine decides to listen to Cyrus this time.
I've been quiet so I know that comment isn't directed at me. I just continue sitting patiently.

"Now. Sinspace is an island belonging to the Demon Laplace, and run by the Goddess Ismalisa. They both are inmates within here, so that means whatever this  place is has strict rules. It necessitates gathering knowledge of your past deeds in order to acquire a vague... sense of redemption- all Ismalisa has told us is that this is for the sake of Redemption. So. With that established. Let us all discuss what this could all mean. And please, correct me if you believe I've stated something poorly. "
"I already knew that."
"I am reestablishing this for ease of discussion, Roshan, something you clearly have never attempted to hold."
"I talk with people all the time, Cyrus..."
"Is- is that why we're here, with all the podiums? Are we supposed to figure something out? I thought Elplace was asking the questions rhetorically."

‚ÄúAbiding by what Ismalisa thinks is right and accepting her worldview, I assume. Roshan‚Äôs sin was just ‚Äòheresy‚Äô, right? I killed a government official, Cyrus wasn‚Äôt good enough as a government official, and both of those disrupt the ‚Äòorder‚Äô of things. Johammad is a societal outcast any religion might discriminate against. Azura and Daryush tried to do something against the teachings of the church. And, uh, I still don‚Äôt know Celine‚Äôs deal.‚Äù
"And we appear to still be missing memories for some reason." Douglas.

‚ÄúThat‚Äôs true. I maybe killed Douglas??? But I have no memory of that, not really, and like, that‚Äôs a huge deal I would be torn up about. Something between retribution and death‚Äôs left all cloudy.‚Äù
"Wait, but what's Douglas' sin?"
I try to remember if he mentioned it.

‚ÄúProbably being affiliated with an organization that‚Äôs evil and annoying, I dunno. I asked him and he went do you truly want to know and because I was still freaking out about the Azura stuff I went no knowing things just hurts me and everything is bad I‚Äôm a huge wuss bluh bluh.‚Äù
"Oh. Maybe you should ask him again now that you're doing better, then."
‚ÄúYeah alright. Douglas, would you be willing to say?‚Äù

"I believe I shall... Refrain at the moment." Douglas.

"We'll get to Douglas's deal later. Right now you all need to focus on the revelation so obvious you've all been dancing around it like fools from minute one." Laplace.
"We aren't dead? We are awful people? This isn't a true afterlife?"
‚ÄúThe fact that you‚Äôre not a real human? I clocked that pretty quickly.‚Äù
‚ÄúOr. I mean, kinda. I didn‚Äôt really get it.‚Äù
"Wait, what did Ebrahim do?"

"Come on. We're not dead and this isn't the afterlife. So what foolish assumption should that call into question?" Laplace.

"Nothing. I failed to ever do anything..." Ebrahim.
I put my chin in my hand in a thinking pose.
